propertyDescriptor.name: Input Directory
propertyDescriptor.description: The input directory from which to pull files

propertyDescriptor.name: File Filter
propertyDescriptor.description: Only files whose names match the given regular expression will be picked up

propertyDescriptor.name: Path Filter
propertyDescriptor.description: When Recurse Subdirectories is true, then only subdirectories whose path matches the given regular expression will be scanned

propertyDescriptor.name: Batch Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum number of files to pull in each iteration

propertyDescriptor.name: Keep Source File
propertyDescriptor.description: If true, the file is not deleted after it has been copied to the Content Repository; this causes the file to be picked up continually and is useful for testing purposes.  If not keeping original NiFi will need write permissions on the directory it is pulling from otherwise it will ignore the file.

propertyDescriptor.name: Recurse Subdirectories
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates whether or not to pull files from subdirectories

propertyDescriptor.name: Polling Interval
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates how long to wait before performing a directory listing

propertyDescriptor.name: Ignore Hidden Files
propertyDescriptor.description: Indicates whether or not hidden files should be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Minimum File Age
propertyDescriptor.description: The minimum age that a file must be in order to be pulled; any file younger than this amount of time (according to last modification date) will be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Maximum File Age
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum age that a file must be in order to be pulled; any file older than this amount of time (according to last modification date) will be ignored

propertyDescriptor.name: Minimum File Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The minimum size that a file must be in order to be pulled

propertyDescriptor.name: Maximum File Size
propertyDescriptor.description: The maximum size that a file can be in order to be pulled

table.feedFormat:
ROW FORMAT SERDE 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.serde2.OpenCSVSerde'
 WITH SERDEPROPERTIES ( 'separatorChar' = ',' ,'escapeChar' = '\\' ,'quoteChar' = '\"') STORED AS TEXTFILE
